news.title: Odisha government suspends two tehsildars for violating plot registration norms
news.para: Earlier, the govt initiated action against 18 sub-registrars who registered 100 or more sub-plots under the development authorities, violating rules.

news.title: Activists in Vasai Virar demand SIT probe into Illegal constructions
news.para: These unauthorised structures are putting excessive pressure on the city's infrastructure, affecting water, electricity, and transport services for legitimate tax-paying residents.

news.title: National Housing Bank expects RMBS firms to raise over Rs 10,000 crore in FY26
news.para: NHB Managing Director and Chief Executive Sanjay Shukla said he expects up to 10 more such transactions in the fiscal year through which lenders will raise between Rs 10,000-12,000 crore.

news.title: Labour shortage due to heatwaves and cement price hike hit construction demand in India
news.para: Prabhudas Lilladher has put out a report after having interacted with cement dealers across regions in India to access the demand and price scenario in April 2025.

news.title: Vardhman Amrante to invest Rs 1,350 crore for realty projects in Punjab in next three years
news.para: The company plans to develop 3-4 projects, Oswal said, adding that these upcoming developments would be in residential, commercial and hospitality segments. These future projects would be certified green buildings.

news.title: SMC officials face heat over rampant illegal constructions in Surat
news.para: The issue came to light during a city coordination meeting on Saturday, where BJP MLA Arvind Rana submitted a written complaint in the presence of municipal commissioner Shalini Agarwal and other city MLAs.

news.title: Delhi: L&DO stalls conversion of leasehold properties to freehold
news.para: As per ministry's annual report for 2020-21, L&DO is responsible for the administration of about 60,526 leases of central govt land in Delhi, out of which 34,905 properties have been converted into freehold.

news.title: Chhattisgarh government announces new reforms in land registration process
news.para: A key feature of the new system is the linking of Aadhaar with both buyers and sellers to prevent fake individuals from selling land illegally.

news.title: Residential sales in Chennai grows 27% in Q1 2025: CREDAI
news.para: The recent reduction in the repo rate by the Reserve Bank of India and the Central government's revised income tax slabs has further supported buyer sentiment, particularly among first time buyers, the report said.

news.title: Punjab and Haryana HC strikes down rule on land surrender, licence forfeiture by developers
news.para: According to the high court, such demands were excessive, legally unsound, and infringed on the developers’ constitutional rights.

news.title: Bagmane Group buys railway land for Rs 1,530 crore in Dwarka, Delhi
news.para: The Rail Land Development Authority (RLDA) had accepted Bagmane's bid to lease the land in 2023, but the deal was delayed due to the need to relocate trees from the site.

news.title: Mysuru civic body's B-khata drive to bring unauthorised properties under tax net
news.para: The civic body aims to bring all 27,616 such properties under the tax net over the next 16 months. This effort is expected to boost property tax revenue.

news.title: Pool, gym NOCs stuck over new rules, but Noida sports department in no mood to relent
news.para: The move follows inspections by officials of the department after several condominiums decided to open their pools, with the NOCs not coming through.

news.title: Karnataka RERA, just a paper tiger: Home buyers
news.para: K-RERA data reveals that of the 1,660 recovery orders issued involving `758.85 crore, only 233 cases have seen action, resulting in a recovery of `91.88 crore.

news.title: Panvel: 96 Pioneer CHS flat owners get eviction notices as building fails to obtain OC
news.para: The corporation recently discontinued their water tanker service, which was being provided free of cost since November 2023, resulting in accumulated costs of Rs 18.54 lakh, despite recurring water tax payment defaults.

news.title: Seal illegal structures even if notices issued: Telangana HC to GHMC
news.para: Justice B Vijaysen Reddy passed this interim order while hearing petition filed by Jijjuvarapu Ramesh who brought to the court's notice one such flagrant violation in OU Colony, Shaikpet wherein a person took permission from GHMC to construct stilt plus two floors but went on raising more floors.

news.title: Mumbai builder gets stop-work notice as residents flag shrinking Walkeshwar Road
news.para: The April 26 notice served to architect Preeti Kashyap Barai and developer Dilip Chunilal Chandan pointed out unauthorised erection of building/execution of work at a plot on the road.
